{
  "plan": 1,
  "meta": {
    "name": "_reference",
    "notes": "Piece-label convention demo. Many examples in one symmetry:none file. Piece id = '<group>-<role>[-<ord>]'. group = <shape><variant> (leading letters = intended shape, trailing digits = instance); everything before the first '-' is the join key; strip trailing digits for the intended label. role: wool=wool-room | lane=corridor piece | room=wide plaza piece | dock=terrain hub (make it >= corridorWidth+1 wide so the flood stops there) | end=terminus piece. entry/cut live in zones[] and are orthogonal to the shape prefix (a cut Z is still shape Z). ord = a,b,c... disambiguator. Groups are offset in x so their terrain never touches; each group is classified in isolation from its own wool room."
  },
